('305466c6-614c-463a-ac9b-2bce591275a0', '1fad8e26-03f9-4368-a2c1-b6e4b9e27c0b', '```\nsrc/\n├── App.jsx                     # Root component — layout + routing\n├── main.jsx                    # React entry point\n├── styles/\n│   └── index.css               # Tailwind + global styles\n│\n├── data/\n│   └── index.js                # All mock data (builds, users, plans, etc.)\n│\n├── components/\n│   ├── ui/\n│   │   ├── Icon.jsx            # SVG icon set (Lucide-style, self-contained)\n│   │   └── SharedUI.jsx        # Badge, C (card), CH (card header), ErrRow,\n│   │                           # Toast, Toggle, exportCSV\n│   │\n│   ├── charts/\n│   │   └── index.jsx           # Spark, BarSVG, SvgBar, SvgGroupBar,\n│   │                           # SvgArea, SvgPie, SvgCpuHistory\n│   │\n│   ├── shared/\n│   │   ├── LogModal.jsx        # Animated build log viewer (used in Admin + Client)\n│   │   ├── Login.jsx           # Login screen (role selector)\n│   │   └── RoleBanner.jsx      # Admin ↔ Client role switcher banner\n│   │\n│   ├── admin/\n│   │   ├── AdminSidebar.jsx    # Sidebar + AdminProfileWidget (Change PW', 1, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
('312044ba-6998-4ee4-9856-eccac90e63ec', 'ad5bf04d-cfdc-4d16-b470-56a7def80128', 'ation\n\nThis section has moved here: [https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/advanced-configuration](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/advanced-configuration)\n\n### Deployment\n\n\n\nThis section has moved here: [https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment)\n\n### `npm run build` fails to minify\n\nThis section has moved here: [https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/troubleshooting#npm-run-build-fails-to-minify](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/troubleshooting#npm-run-build-fails-to-minify)', 3, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('32813e64-889a-43b4-a775-74b221cd8138', 'cbb4429c-2b30-4fb4-bec7-8d7342f9b75d', 'type definitions (User, LikeLemba, Goal, Transaction, etc.)\r\n- Configured Vite environment types\r\n\r\n### Internationalization\r\n- Installed and configured react-i18next\r\n- Extracted all translations from hardcoded strings\r\n- Created separate translation files (en.json, fr.json)\r\n- Implemented proper i18n configuration\r\n\r\n### API Layer\r\n- Created abstraction layer for all API calls\r\n- Implemented ApiClient with token management\r\n- Created service modules (auth, circles, goals, transactions)\r\n- Added proper error handling and TypeScript types\r\n- Implemented token storage and refresh logic\r\n\r\n### UI Components\r\n- Created reusable UI components (Button, Input, Card, Badge, Modal)\r\n- Built layout components (Header, BottomNavigation)\r\n- Implemented consistent styling with Tailwind CSS\r\n- Added proper TypeScript props and interfaces\r\n\r\n### Pages\r\n- Created page components (Home, Circles, Wallet, Card, Profile)\r\n- Implemented proper page structure with headers\r\n- Set up placeholder content for migration\r\n\r\n### Security\r\n- Comprehensive security review documented in SECURITY_REVIEW.md\r\n- Identified critical vulnerabilities in auth and payment flows\r\n- Documented recommendations for secure i', 2, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('33702410-096c-466e-89f7-4caa79aecd38', 'd7f25929-c07b-458f-bd4c-6f6a89fdc212', 'bout [deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment) for more information.\n\n### `npm run eject`\n\n**Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you `eject`, you can\'t go back!**\n\n\n\nIf you aren\'t satisfied with the build tool and configuration choices, you can `eject` at any time. This command will remove the single build dependency from your project.\n\nInstead, it will copy all the configuration files and the transitive dependencies (webpack, Babel, ESLint, etc) right into your project so you have full control over them. All of the commands except `eject` will still work, but they will point to the copied scripts so you can tweak them. At this point you\'re on your own.\n\nYou don\'t have to ever use `eject`. The curated feature set is suitable for small and middle deployments, and you shouldn\'t feel obligated to use this feature. However we understand that this tool wouldn\'t be useful if you couldn\'t customize it when you are ready for it.\n\n## Learn More\n\nYou can learn more in the [Create React App documentation](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/getting-started).\n\nTo learn React, check out the [React documentation](https://reactjs.org/).', 1, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('33a4dac3-3b6b-4784-b786-68fb1bd6fd9e', '399fd314-6581-4c4b-a300-01873157cce5', 'ToastContext.tsx          → Toasts visuels\ndata/\n  recipes.ts               → 116 recettes parsées\nhooks/                     → Hooks personnalisés\ntypes/                     → Types TypeScript\n```\n\n\n\n## Lancer en développement\n\n```bash\n# Installer les dépendances\nnpm install\n\n# Lancer le serveur de développement\nnpx expo start\n\n# Scanner le QR code avec Expo Go (iOS/Android)\n```\n\n## Build pour les stores\n\n### Prérequis\n\n1. Installer EAS CLI :\n```bash\nnpm install -g eas-cli\n```\n\n2. Se connecter à son compte Expo :\n```bash\neas login\n```\n\n3. Configurer le projet (une seule fois) :\n```bash\neas build:configure\n```\n\n### Build iOS (App Store)\n\n```bash\n# Build de production pour iOS\neas build --platform ios --profile production\n\n# Soumettre sur l\'App Store\neas submit --platform ios\n```\n\n> **Note :** Un compte Apple Developer (99$/an) est requis.\n\n### Build Android (Google Play)\n\n```bash\n# Build de production pour Android (AAB)\neas build --platform android --profile production\n\n# Soumettre sur le Google Play Store\neas submit --platform android\n```\n\n> **Note :** Un compte Google Play Developer (25$ one-time) est requis.\n\n### Build les deux plateformes', 2, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
('346e7768-3e45-415c-bb19-a5affdc33839', '9104cc1a-4756-4208-87e6-2a5cfebf7940', 'PR #1: Master\nState: closed\nLabels:', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('34bc08ab-657d-4b95-a48d-647053f9a124', '207b7e46-fbe5-425e-829d-d4ddaa266630', 'Issue #2: Claude/review project m vnwt\nState: closed\nLabels: \n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nImplement end-to-end email-based authentication and verification flow across frontend and backend, expand user domain model, and document integration status and implementation progress.\n\nNew Features:\n- Add email-based registration, login, and verification flows on the frontend with dedicated Login, Register, and VerifyEmail pages wired into the router.\n- Introduce structured registration and verification response types and updated auth service methods to align with the new backend API contracts.\n- Expose new public auth routes (/login, /register, /verify-email) and export corresponding page components for app-wide use.\n- Define stub backend controllers for payments, goals, transactions, notifications, and referrals to scaffold future API functionality.\n\nEnhancements:\n- Extend the users table schema to include separate first/last names, phone, referral, plan tier, balances, and KYC-related fields.\n- Configure Laravel API routing and CORS middleware for the new API routes file and remove the legacy CORS config.\n- Implement a backend UserController with endpoints for profile retrieval, profile updates, password/passcode changes, and KYC document upload.\n- Align auth data contracts with backend expectations by switching to email-based login, adding password confirmation, and verifying email via user_id/OTP.\n\nDocumentation:\n- Add detailed integration status, test results, and implementation com', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19');
