('582fa599-84dc-41d7-bb47-99c401ed71cb', '983f05f6-8803-4cf0-8a89-0ad95439e768', 'PR #5: Claude/review project m vnwt\nState: closed\nLabels: \n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nEnable real email delivery for OTP verification and expand frontend screens to consume additional app context for savings circles and LikeLemba flows.\n\nNew Features:\n- Send OTP verification codes via email using the configured mailer instead of only logging them.\n\nBug Fixes:\n- Wire the profile logout button directly to the authentication logout function.\n\nEnhancements:\n- Expose additional user and LikeLemba/circle fields from global app context to the Home, Wallet, Profile, and Goals screens for richer UI behavior.\n- Add support for finished circles and circle selection state in the wallet view.\n- Include active LikeLemba information in the goals page logic.', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('5936d01c-c4ef-40d2-bf5c-a02c84de825e', '72721bad-9495-443f-96d0-76fc79c0b473', 'PR #4: feat: Extract all screens from original App.tsx into separate page files\nState: closed\nLabels: \n\n- Created AppContext with all shared state (circles, goals, notifications, transactions, user info, support tickets, security logs, live chat, group chats)\r\n- Updated BottomNavigation to match original design with center elevated Join button\r\n- Updated routes with React Router tab sync and /goals route\r\n- Home.tsx: HomeScreen, NotificationsScreen, WhatsHotScreen\r\n- Circles.tsx: CirclesScreen, JoinScreen, and 21 sub-screens (all create/join flows, group chat, referral, likelemba details, payout methods)\r\n- Wallet.tsx: PaymentsScreen and 10 sub-screens (transaction history, financial dashboard, payment settings, saved cards)\r\n- Card.tsx: CardScreen with virtual card display, freeze/unfreeze, top-up flow, payment method management\r\n- Profile.tsx: ProfileScreen and 16 sub-screens (personal info, documents, security, support, live chat, FAQ)\r\n- Goals.tsx: MyGoalsScreen and 6 sub-screens (goal detail, create goal, saving programs, plan upgrade)\r\n- All original JSX layouts and designs preserved exactly as-is\r\n\r\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01DQYEizP5oC7ge3u6Uq7Tpu', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
('59a904ef-d3f9-4fab-8fdc-d6a5fe4a8458', 'aa656288-06bd-4cfd-a37d-1bb7ef3df988', 'PR #2: Claude/review chatbot 1 i2q3\nState: closed\nLabels:\n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nRevamp the NovAI chat and auth interfaces with a new visual design and UX improvements, including enhanced message rendering and onboarding.\n\nNew Features:\n- Add quick-start suggestion cards on the welcome screen that prefill and submit example prompts.\n- Introduce code block headers with language labels and copy-to-clipboard controls in assistant messages.\n- Enable textarea-based message input with auto-resize and Enter-to-send behavior.\n- Add mobile sidebar overlay behavior and improved sidebar toggling for small screens.', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('59f3c7f2-0810-4754-bb88-223fee2ec69d', '0e35f5ba-f25d-41c1-8497-cbea702b32e6', '# Getting Started with Create React App\n\nThis project was bootstrapped with [Create React App](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app).\n\n## Available Scripts\n\nIn the project directory, you can run:\n\n### `npm start`\n\nRuns the app in the development mode.\\\nOpen [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.\n\nThe page will reload when you make changes.\\\nYou may also see any lint errors in the console.\n\n### `npm test`\n\nLaunches the test runner in the interactive watch mode.\\\nSee the section about [running tests](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests) for more information.\n\n### `npm run build`\n\nBuilds the app for production to the `build` folder.\\\nIt correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.\n\nThe build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.\\\nYour app is ready to be deployed!\n\nSee the section about [deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment) for more information.\n\n### `npm run eject`\n\n**Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you `eject`, you can\'t go back!**', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
