('cb5f3116-1763-4f20-8e47-2361e3b16107', 'd20d5e11-2f46-4890-a45f-149f0c64cc93', '# python\nfor sysadmin\nThis tiny code allows us to find the open ports on machine and do the whois. Let\'s enjoy to that.', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('ccebe8f2-c4b6-490e-839d-b1b3404fc65a', '44abc6d0-e203-4258-ae79-9c066798d21a', 'Design\n- Palette : Navy (#0B1D3A) + Gold (#F5A623) + Blue (#1A56DB)\n- Style Money Fellows adapté pour le Congo\n- Icônes SVG (pas d\'emojis)\n- Responsive : plein écran mobile, cadre téléphone desktop\n\n\n\n## 🛠 Stack\n- React 18 + Vite\n- Single-file architecture (pas de dépendances UI)\n- Prêt pour découpage en modules\n\n## 📞 Contact\n- Lamuka Tech · Brazzaville, Congo\n- business@lamuka-tech.com\n- +242 06 466 3469\n\n© 2026 Lamuka Tech. Tous droits réservés.', 2, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
('cda998f1-4307-4b01-9c94-3084c16bc3bb', 'a3b920f2-a78e-423e-ac6d-3a49f674576a', 'PR #1: Claude/review chatbot 1 i2q3\nState: closed\nLabels: \n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nIntroduce a full Flask-based web chatbot application powered by local Ollama models with persistent multi-conversation support and user accounts.\n\nNew Features:\n- Add a Flask web app that streams responses from a local Ollama model with conversation history and per-user context.\n- Implement user registration, login, and logout with password hashing and session-based authentication.\n- Provide multi-conversation management with titles, deletion, and export to text files per user.\n- Add a rich chat UI with sidebar conversation list, Markdown rendering, syntax-highlighted code blocks, and typing indicators.\n\nEnhancements:\n- Introduce a SQLite-backed persistence layer for users, conversations, and messages with helper access functions.\n\nBuild:\n- Add Python runtime dependencies for Flask, requests, and python-dotenv in requirements.txt.\n\nDocumentation:\n- Expand README with French setup, configuration, and usage instructions for running the local Ollama-powered chatbot.', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('ce278e91-6f37-484c-9f72-5eda96d9026f', '93eb695f-9891-4262-a7a6-375b8b226fb2', '--profile production\n\n# Soumettre sur le Google Play Store\neas submit --platform android\n```\n\n> **Note :** Un compte Google Play Developer (25$ one-time) est requis.\n\n### Build les deux plateformes\n\n\n\n```bash\neas build --platform all --profile production\n```\n\n### Configuration `eas.json`\n\nCréez `eas.json` à la racine si absent :\n\n```json\n{\n  \"cli\": {\n    \"version\": \">= 3.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"build\": {\n    \"development\": {\n      \"developmentClient\": true,\n      \"distribution\": \"internal\"\n    },\n    \"preview\": {\n      \"distribution\": \"internal\"\n    },\n    \"production\": {}\n  },\n  \"submit\": {\n    \"production\": {}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Build de développement (recommandé pour tester les modules natifs)\n\n```bash\neas build --platform ios --profile development\neas build --platform android --profile development\n```\n\n## Auteur\n\n**Leonel Ngoya** — [lndev.me](https://lndev.me)\n\n## Licence\n\nProjet privé — © 2025 Leonel Ngoya', 3, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20');
