('da20bb81-7880-4e86-94c3-c069668e752e', 'ab0de836-8559-4aea-abb0-8e1ea5a6b07d', 'Issue #6: Claude/review project m vnwt\nState: closed\nLabels:\n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nIntegrate the frontend with new and existing backend APIs for circles, goals, cards, notifications, payments, and support, replacing demo data and local-only state updates with persisted server-driven data flows.\n\nNew Features:\n- Add backend-powered circle chat, membership management, and join/create flows that load and persist data via circlesService.\n- Introduce goal contribution, withdrawal, and deletion capabilities wired to backend goalsService with a reusable contribution modal.\n- Implement virtual card top-up and freeze/unfreeze actions backed by cardService with real balance retrieval.\n- Add full CRUD support for payment methods using a dedicated paymentMethodsService.\n- Introduce paymentsService and supportService to handle contributions and support tickets via backend APIs.\n- Add notificationsService to synchronize notification read state with the server and fetch real notifications.\n- Expose global loading, error, and refreshData handling in AppContext tied to authenticated user data fetching.', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('db1d151d-93bf-43ec-8b88-59ec719fd1b1', '6e657ebd-5c4d-4f5a-bbc0-4c95ec2f5419', '# Getting Started with Create React App\n\nThis project was bootstrapped with [Create React App](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app).\n\n## Available Scripts\n\nIn the project directory, you can run:\n\n### `npm start`\n#this helps me to download MS office: https://github.com/alsyundawy/Microsoft-Office-For-MacOS/tree/master\nRuns the app in the development mode.\\\nOpen [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.\n\nThe page will reload when you make changes.\\\nYou may also see any lint errors in the console.\n\n### `npm test`\n\nLaunches the test runner in the interactive watch mode.\\\nSee the section about [running tests](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests) for more information.\n\n### `npm run build`\n\nBuilds the app for production to the `build` folder.\\\nIt correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.\n\nThe build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.\\\nYour app is ready to be deployed!\n\nSee the section about [deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment) for more information.\n\n### `npm run eject`\n\n**Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you `eject`, you can\'t go back!**\n\nIf you aren\'t satisfied with the build tool and configuration choices, you can `eject` at any time. This command will remove the single build dependency from your project.\n\nInstead, it will copy all the configuration files and the transitive dependencies (webpack, Babel, ES', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:19'),
