('fd6bb6b9-5a9c-4ea4-b224-80413777d63a', '9d2d58a0-4639-47d0-ba70-adf4b88614c4', 'start your _Android_ or _iOS_ app:\n\n### For Android\n\n```bash\n# using npm\nnpm run android\n\n# OR using Yarn\nyarn android\n```\n\n### For iOS\n\n```bash\n# using npm\nnpm run ios\n\n# OR using Yarn\nyarn ios\n```\n\n\n\nIf everything is set up _correctly_, you should see your new app running in your _Android Emulator_ or _iOS Simulator_ shortly provided you have set up your emulator/simulator correctly.\n\nThis is one way to run your app — you can also run it directly from within Android Studio and Xcode respectively.\n\n## Step 3: Modifying your App\n\nNow that you have successfully run the app, let\'s modify it.\n\n1. Open `App.tsx` in your text editor of choice and edit some lines.\n2. For **Android**: Press the <kbd>R</kbd> key twice or select **\"Reload\"** from the **Developer Menu** (<kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>M</kbd> (on Window and Linux) or <kbd>Cmd ⌘</kbd> + <kbd>M</kbd> (on macOS)) to see your changes!\n\nFor **iOS**: Hit <kbd>Cmd ⌘</kbd> + <kbd>R</kbd> in your iOS Simulator to reload the app and see your changes!\n\n## Congratulations! :tada:\n\nYou\'ve successfully run and modified your React Native App. :partying_face:\n\n### Now what?', 1, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
('fe3405b6-a7a8-4803-9e7b-4a6c38a465a0', 'a34d09b2-c585-4526-8783-86e1ad2c055a', 'PR #6: Claude/review project m vnwt\nState: closed\nLabels: \n\n## Summary by Sourcery\n\nIntegrate the frontend with new and existing backend APIs for circles, goals, cards, notifications, payments, and support, replacing demo data and local-only state updates with persisted server-driven data flows.\n\nNew Features:\n- Add backend-powered circle chat, membership management, and join/create flows that load and persist data via circlesService.\n- Introduce goal contribution, withdrawal, and deletion capabilities wired to backend goalsService with a reusable contribution modal.\n- Implement virtual card top-up and freeze/unfreeze actions backed by cardService with real balance retrieval.\n- Add full CRUD support for payment methods using a dedicated paymentMethodsService.\n- Introduce paymentsService and supportService to handle contributions and support tickets via backend APIs.\n- Add notificationsService to synchronize notification read state with the server and fetch real notifications.\n- Expose global loading, error, and refreshData handling in AppContext tied to authenticated user data fetching.\n\nEnhancements:\n- Replace seeded demo data in AppContext with real backend-driven initialization for circles, goals, transactions, notifications, and support tickets.\n- Update Home, Circles, Goals, Card, and Profile screens to consume backend data, improve error handling, and remove hardcoded copy in some profile sections.\n\nDocumentation:\n- Add BACKEND_INTEGRATION_STATUS and MISSING_FEATURES do', 0, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:20'),
