('msg_1777201070232_assistant', 'sysaudio_conv_1777201046120_4ps2l7jp9', 'assistant', '**Code Summary**\n\nThe provided code defines a React component named `BorderBeam`. This component generates a customizable animated border beam effect.\n\n**Key Features**\n\n* The component accepts several props:\n  * `duration`: animation duration (default: 3.5 seconds)\n  * `delay`: animation delay (default: 0 seconds)\n  * `colorFrom` and `colorTo`: colors for the gradient (defaults: \'transparent\' and \'rgba(99,102,241,0.9)\')\n  * `size`: beam size (default: 30)\n\n**Functionality**\n\nThe component renders a nested `<span>` structure. The inner `<span>` element has an animated linear gradient background that moves horizontally, creating a beam effect. The animation is defined using CSS and has the following properties:\n\n* `animation-name`: `borderBeam`\n* `animation-duration`: specified by the `duration` prop\n* `animation-delay`: specified by the `delay` prop\n* `animation-timing-function`: linear\n* `animation-iteration-count`: infinite\n\n**Optimal Approach and Complexity**\n\nThe code uses a straightforward approach to create the animated border beam effect. The time complexity of this code is $O(1)$, as it only involves rendering a static component with predefined styles. The space complexity is also $O(1)$, as it only uses a constant amount of space to store the component\'s props and styles. \n\n**Code Quality**\n\nThe code is well-structured and concise. However, the animation definition is not explicitly provided in the code snippet. It is assumed that the `@keyframes borderBeam` animation is defined elsewhere in the stylesheet. \n\nHere is a reformatted version of your code with improved documentation:\n\n```typescript\nimport { useEffect, useRef } from \'react\';\n\n/**\n * Props interface for the BorderBeam component.\n */\ninterface BorderBeamProps {\n  /**\n   * Animation duration in seconds (default: 3.5).\n   */\n  duration?: number;\n  /**\n   * Animation delay in seconds (default: 0).\n   */\n  delay?: number;\n  /**\n   * Starting color of the gradient (default: \'transparent\').\n   */\n  colorFrom?: string;\n  /**\n   * Ending color of the gradient (default: \'rgba(99,102,241,0.9)\').\n   */\n  colorTo?: string;\n  /**\n   * Beam size in percentage (default: 30).\n   */\n  size?: number;\n}\n\n/**\n * A customizable animated border beam component.\n */\nexport function BorderBeam({\n  duration = 3.5,\n  delay = 0,\n  colorFrom = \'transparent\',\n  colorTo = \'rgba(99,102,241,0.9)\',\n  size = 30,\n}: BorderBeamProps) {\n  return (\n    <span\n      className=\"pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden rounded-[inherit]\"\n      style={{ zIndex: 10 }}\n    >\n      <span\n        style={{\n          position: \'absolute\',\n          top: 0,\n          left: 0,\n          width: `${size}%`,\n          height: \'1.5px\',\n          background: `linear-gradient(90deg, ${colorFrom}, ${colorTo}, ${colorFrom})`,\n          animation: `borderBeam ${duration}s ${delay}s linear infinite`,\n          borderRadius: \'999px\',\n        }}\n      />\n    </span>\n  );\n}\n```', 1777201070232, NULL, 'tauri', '2026-04-26 15:37:16'),
