INSERT INTO `messages` (`id`, `conversation_id`, `role`, `content`, `timestamp`, `attached_files`, `source`, `imported_at`) VALUES
('msg_1779562133373_assistant', 'sysaudio_conv_1779562093136_el53f3enz', 'assistant', ' Good to know\n\nsome lines.\n2. For **Android**: Press the <kbd>R</kbd> key twice or select **\"Reload\"** from the **Developer Menu** (<kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>M</s\n\n[4] from conversations:\nUser: i have a react native project that uses typescript \nUser: i need to run the app on my iphone\nRunning a React Native app on an iPhone involves several steps. First, ensure you have Xcode installed on your Mac. Then, you\'ll need to prepare your project for iOS development.\n\n## Step 1: Install Xcode\n Ensure you have the latest version of Xcode installed. You can download it from the Mac App Store.\n\n## Step 2: Open the Project in Xcode\n Open your project\'s `ios` folder in Xcode. This folder contains the iOS-specific code for your React Native project.\n\n## Step 3: Configure the Project in Xcode\n In Xcode, make sure you\'ve selected the correct target (your app\'s name) and that the bundle identifier matches the one in your `Info.plist` file.\n\n## Step 4: Connect Your iPhone\n Connect your iPhone to your Mac using a USB cable.\n\n## Step 5: Select the iPhone as the Build Device\n In Xcode, select your iPhone from the list of available devices.\n\n## Step 6: Run the App\n Click the \"Play\" button or press ⌘ + R to run the app on your iPhone.\n\n## Step 7: Trust the App\n If prompted, trust the app on your iPhone by going to Settings > General > Profiles and finding your developer profile.\n\n## Step 8: Run Metro\n Make sure Metro (the JavaScript bundler) is running. You can start it by running `npx react-native start` in your terminal.\n\n## Step 9: Build and Run\n After completing the above steps, you should be able to build and run your React Native app on your iPhone.\n\n# Additional Tips:\n- Ensure your iPhone is unlocked and the screen is on.\n- If you encounter any issues, check the React Native documentation or community forums for solutions.\n\nDo you need more detailed instructions on any of these steps?\n\nAlso, ensure you have the Apple Developer account and necessary certificates set up if you plan to distribute the app outside of your local development environment.', 1779562133373, NULL, 'tauri', '2026-05-25 00:43:18'),
